@node "Intr" "Introduction"

 YAM (abbreviation for 'Yet Another Mailer') is a combined Mailer/POP/SMTP
 client for the Amiga.

 @{B}Features of YAM:@{UB}

 - Basic functions: read, write, delete, reply and forward mail
 - Three @{"folders" link "NdMA"} for incoming, outgoing and sent mail and up to
   48 folders for archived mail
 - @{"Address book" link "NdAB"} supporting groups and user lists
 - Built-in @{"POP3" link "Mail"} client to check for mail on startup, on demand or at
   regular time intervals
 - Write or reply your messages off line and send them to the mail server
   using the built-in @{"SMTP" link "Mail"} client
 - Add the sender of a message to the address book with a simple mouseclick
 - Built-in support for UUencode and @{"MIME" link "MIME"} to send and receive binary files
 - Up to 48 filters to automatically process new messages
 - The @{"ARexx port" link "Rexx"} allows other programs (e.g. WWW browsers) to control YAM
 - YAM is a commodity: it waits in the background as an icon and pops up
   when a hotkey is pressed
 - The graphical user interface of YAM is programmed with @{"MUI" link "MUI"} and is
   therefore font-sensitive; the windows are freely sizeable
 - YAM runs either on the Workbench screen or on any other custom screen
 - Context related on line help through help bubbles and AmigaGuide
 - 15 supported languages
 - Easy @{"installation" link "Inst"} with the Installer
@endnode

@node "Reqs" "Requirements"

 @{b}HARDWARE REQUIREMENTS@{ub}

 - Amiga Computer with a minimum of 1 MB Ram


 @{b}NEEDED SOFTWARE@{ub}

 - Kickstart 2.0/Workbench 2.0 or higher for the English version
 - Kickstart 2.0/Workbench 2.1 or higher for the non-English versions
 - @{"MUI 3.3" link "MUI"} or higher
 - AmiTCP compatible stack (AmiTCP, Miami or TermiteTCP)
@endnode

